raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "MOCPy" %}
{% set version = "0.18.0" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/mocpy-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: d989a7bb66505600bb2682cef6f2eaf3c6005138a751082b15f34978752fa24c

build:
  number: 0
  skip: true  # [python_impl == 'pypy']
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - crossenv                               # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - maturin >=1.3.2,<2                     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
    - {{ stdlib("c") }}
    - {{ compiler("rust") }}
  host:
    - pip
    - toml
    - maturin >=1.3.2,<2
    - python
  run:
    - astropy-base
    - regions
    - numpy
    - cdshealpix
    - matplotlib-base
    - networkx
    - requests
    - python

test:
  files:
    - mocpy_test.py
  imports:
    - mocpy
  commands:
    - pip check
    - python mocpy_test.py
  requires:
    - pip
    - python
    - pytest

about:
  home: https://github.com/cds-astro/mocpy
  summary: MOC parsing and manipulation in Python
  license_family: BSD
  license: BSD-3-Clause
